Subject: [PATCH] Don't force_load static xcframework imports

Two of our SPM deps each ship an ios-arm64 static archive that
statically embeds the Rust standard library plus the `object`
crate:

  * tkey-ios's       libtkey.xcframework/ios-arm64/libtkey.a
  * curvelib.swift's curve_secp256k1.xcframework/ios-arm64/libsecp256k1_rs.a

rules_swift_package_manager generates `alwayslink = True` for every
static xcframework import, which translates to `-force_load <archive>`
at link time. With both archives force-loaded, ld pulls every .o from
both — producing ~3500 duplicate-symbol errors for the shared Rust
stdlib / `object` crate symbols. Disabling `alwayslink` lets ld load
symbols on demand and the collisions resolve naturally (ld picks up
the symbols from the first archive that defines them and skips the
already-defined copies in the second).

TODO(nicegram): drop this patch (and the `single_version_override`
in MODULE.bazel that applies it) once upstream removes the explicit
`alwayslink = True` on static xcframework imports. The xcframework
case is part of the same removal pass tracked in
https://github.com/cgrindel/rules_swift_package_manager/issues/2216
(post-rules_swift-3.0, alwayslink becomes the default and these
explicit attributes become redundant).

--- a/swiftpkg/internal/swiftpkg_build_files.bzl
+++ b/swiftpkg/internal/swiftpkg_build_files.bzl
@@ -965,9 +965,6 @@
         ]
         kind = apple_kinds.static_xcframework_import
 
-        # Firebase example requires that GoogleAppMeasurement symbols are
-        # passed along.
-        attrs["alwayslink"] = True
     elif artifact_info.link_type == link_types.dynamic:
         load_stmts = [
             apple_dynamic_xcframework_import_load_stmt,
